President Obama announced the nomination of several individuals for key administration posts. Joseph Westphal was nominated for Under Secretary of the Army, Department of Defense; Robert V. Abbey for Director of the Bureau of Land Management, Department of the Interior; Sam D. Hamilton for Director of the Office of Fish and Wildlife Service, Department of the Interior; Deborah A. P. Hersman for Chairman of the National Transportation Safety Board; Richard A. Lidinsky, Jr. for Commissioner of the Federal Maritime Commission; and Harry Hoglander was re-nominated to serve as a Board Member of the National Mediation Board. President Obama expressed gratitude for their service and stated that their collective backgrounds and experiences will contribute to the nation's safety and prosperity. The article provides details about the qualifications and experiences of each nominee.